Req. No. 16432 Page 9

1 5. Any official court reporter who is the holder of more than
2 one certification shall be compensated in the additional amounts
3 specified in paragraphs 1 through 4 of this subsection for each
4 certification up to a maximum of Eight Thousand Dollars ($8,000.00)
5 per year over and above the reporter's base salary, payable monthly.
6 E. In the event of a lapse in a court reporter's certification,
7 compensation for that certification as provided for in subsection D
8 of this section which is over and above the court reporter's salary
9 shall be suspended until the certification is renewed or reinstated.
10 Compensation shall not be paid to a court reporter for any period
11 during which the court reporter's certification was not in good
12 standing.
13 F. Court reporters temporarily employed by the district court,
14 Workers' Compensation Court of Existing Claims, or Corporation
15 Commission shall be compensated by the court fund of the court which
16 they serve at a rate to be set by such court. In addition, court
17 reporters temporarily employed pursuant to this subsection who are
18 required by the terms of their employment to travel outside their
19 county of residence shall receive reimbursement for mileage actually
20 and necessarily traveled to and from the place of attendance at a
21 rate not to exceed the rate of reimbursement specified in the State
22 Travel Reimbursement Act for state employees. Any travel
23 reimbursement shall be paid from the court fund of the court where
24 the service of the temporarily employed court reporter is provided.
Req. No. 16432 Page 10

1 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 20 O.S. 2021, Section 1503, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 1503. A. Every applicant who seeks to be examined for
4 enrollment as a certified shorthand reporter shall prove to the
5 satisfaction of the State Board of Examiners of Certified Shorthand
6 Reporters that he or she:
7 1. Is of legal age;
8 2. Meets the requisite standards of ethical fitness; and
9 3. Has at least a high school education or its equivalent.
10 B. The examination for certification in one or more authorized
11 methods of shorthand reporting consists of two parts, designated
12 Part 1 and Part 2 as follows:
13 1. Part 1 consists of the test as authorized by the Supreme
14 Court consisting of the following requirements: demonstrated
15 proficiency in reporting testimony and proceedings at a speed of not
16 more than two hundred (200) words per minute in taking a question-
17 and-answer-type dictation and at a speed of not more than one
18 hundred eighty (180) words per minute in taking literary materials
19 which shall be designed to test the ability of an applicant to
20 accurately prepare a transcript of testimony and proceedings that is
21 reasonably free from spelling errors. The Board may not increase or
22 decrease such minimum speed requirement, by rule or otherwise; and
23 2. Part 2 is the Oklahoma Written Knowledge test Test which
24 consists of not less than twenty-five multiple choice questions
Req. No. 16432 Page 11

1 rela ting to Oklahoma law and court rules, duties of certified
2 shorthand reporters, and general court procedure.
3 The examination shall be approved by the Supreme Court. A
4 person who has tested with the Board and successfully completed the
5 written knowledge portion of the examination shall be allowed to
6 retain the credit for that portion for two (2) years from the date
7 passed, and shall not be required to retake that portion during the
8 two-year period.
9 C. An applicant who is academically dishonest when taking any
10 authorized examination is disqualified and may not take the
11 examination again until two (2) years have elapsed from the date of
12 the examination at which the applicant was disqualified.
13 D. A certification issued under this section must be for one or
14 more of the following methods of shorthand reporting:
15 1. Written shorthand;
16 2. Machine shorthand;
17 2. Stenomask shorthand; or
18 3. Any other method of shorthand reporting authorized by the
19 Supreme Court.
20 E. No person may engage in shorthand reporting in this state
21 unless the person is a licensed or certified shorthand reporter or
22 otherwise authorized by law or the Supreme Court.
23 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
Req. No. 16432 Page 12

1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
